Hallett, 1996; Ho, 1996) and adopted operationally in Malaysia. Knowledge of interactions between APW and CRB may influence how operational trapping programmes are developed and implemented.
Trapping protocols for APW in date palm plantings in desert regions have been established by other researchers in the Middle East (Abozuhairah et al., 1996). Herein we present the results of studies designed to develop pheromone-based masstrapping protocols for APW in coconut plantations in the humid tropics, where CRB co-exists with APW. Results of a trap design experiment for use in date palm plantings are also presented.

